---
import InterviewLayout from '../../layouts/InterviewLayout.astro';
import InterviewCard from '../../components/interview/InterviewCard.astro';
import codeCssGridPng from '../../assets/portfolio/images/interview/css/grid.png';
import codeCssScssPng from '../../assets/portfolio/images/interview/css/scss.png';
---

<InterviewLayout title="HTML & CSS" currentTab="html-css">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 items-start">
    
    <InterviewCard title="Local storage" class="md:col-span-1">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>Browser storage to store data in key value pair</li>
        <li>10MB data can be stored with No expiration date</li>
        <li>
          <div class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1 block bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded text-sm font-mono">
            localStorage.setItem("lastname", "bansal");<br />
            localStorage.getItem("lastname");<br />
            localStorage.removeItem("lastname");
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Session storage" class="md:col-span-1">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>Similar to Local storage but for a session only</li>
        <li>data will be removed once tab or browser is closed</li>
        <li>
          <div class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1 block bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded text-sm font-mono">
            sessionStorage.setItem("lastname", "bansal");<br />
            sessionStorage.getItem("lastname");<br />
            sessionStorage.removeItem("lastname");
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Cookies More secure" class="md:col-span-1">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          Key-value storage that stores values as string and Up to 4KB data can be stored
        </li>
        <li>
          Have expiration time, if no expiration time is given then the cookie will get expired at the end of the browser session.
        </li>
        <li>
          They reduce manipulation by client-side JavaScript: You can restrict client-side access by setting the HttpOnly flag. So they prevent client side scripting attacks
        </li>
        <li>
          If you need to store data that is accessible for both the server and the client, use cookies. Otherwise, use local storage.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1">Uses : </span>
          Storing User Preferences , jwt tokens , session status
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1 block bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded text-sm font-mono">
            document.cookie="name=sarthak"
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="IndexedDB" class="md:col-span-1">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>Can store both objects and key-value pairs Up to 250MB</li>
        <li>Do not have expiration time unless explicit deletion</li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1">Uses : </span>
          When need to store a large number of objects which is time-consuming and a lag on performance to convert to string for Local Storage every time.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Flexbox" class="md:col-span-2">
      <h5 class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-2">Parent element or Flex-container properties:</h5>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li><span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">display : flex;</span></li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-direction: row;</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm ml-2">// wrap , wrap-reverse</span>
        </li>
        <li><span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-wrap: nowrap</span></li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-flow: row nowrap; </span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm ml-2">- shorthand for setting both flex-direction and flex-wrap</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">justify-content: flex-start;</span>
          <br/>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm ml-6">// (Horizontally aligns) flex-end, space-around, space-between, space-evenly, center</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">align-items: stretch;</span>
          <br/>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm ml-6">// (Vertically aligns) center, flex-start, flex-end, baseline</span>
        </li>
        <li><span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">align-content: </span></li>
      </ul>

      <h5 class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-2">child element or Flex-item properties:</h5>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">align-self</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">Specifies the alignment for a flex item (overrides the flex container's align-items property)</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-basis : 200px</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">Specifies the initial length of a flex item</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-grow : 0</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">Specifies how much a flex item will grow relative to the rest of the flex items inside the same container</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex-shrink : 0</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">Specifies how much a flex item will shrink relative to the rest of the flex items inside the same container</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">flex: grow shrink basis</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">A shorthand property for the flex-grow, flex-shrink, and the flex-basis properties</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="text-blue-600 font-mono">order</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm block ml-6">Specifies the order of the flex items inside the same container</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Grid Layout" class="md:col-span-2">
      <img src={codeCssGridPng.src} alt="grid layout" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-100" />
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="SASS / SCSS" class="md:col-span-1">
      <img src={codeCssScssPng.src} alt="sass scss" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-100" />
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Accessibility" class="md:col-span-1">
      <h5 class="text-red-500 font-semibold">in progress</h5>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Browser Api" class="md:col-span-1">
      <h5 class="text-red-500 font-semibold">in progress</h5>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Data attribute" class="md:col-span-1">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
        Data-attributes-The data-* attribute is used to store custom data private to the page or application.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
        The stored (custom) data can then be used in the page's JavaScript to create a more engaging user experience (without any Ajax calls or server-side database queries).
      </p>
      <div class="text-red-500 font-mono text-sm bg-red-50 p-2 rounded">
        &lt;div id='person' data-name="sarthak" data-age="28"&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;…<br />
        &lt;/div&gt;<br />
        <br />
        element.dataset.name; // "sarthak"
      </div>
    </InterviewCard>

    <InterviewCard title="Defer Async" class="md:col-span-1">
      <div class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        When the browser loads HTML and comes across a <span class="text-gray-500 font-mono">&lt;script&gt;...&lt;/script&gt;</span> tag, it can't continue building the DOM. It must execute the script first internal or external doesnt matter.it leads to some problems.
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2">
          <li>Scripts can't find DOM elements below them, so they can't add handlers etc.</li>
          <li>it make website load slower as script is blocking page load</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <h5 class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1">Defer (better in most cases)</h5>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 text-sm">
        with defer attribute browser donot wait for the script to load Instead, the browser will continue to process the HTML & build DOM. The script loads “in the background”, and then runs when the DOM is fully built. Scripts with defer always execute when the DOM is ready (but before DOMContentLoaded event). They executed in Document order
      </p>
      <h5 class="text-blue-600 font-bold mb-1">Async</h5>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
        Similar to defer, async scripts load in the background and run when ready.Load-first order. Their document order doesn't matter - which loads first runs first
      </p>
    </InterviewCard>

  </div>
</InterviewLayout>
